Here's a JavaScript function that lists the numbers above or equal to 3 from an array:

```javascript
function listNumbersAboveThree(numbers) {
  var result = [];

  for (var i = 0; i < numbers.length; i++) {
    if (numbers[i] >= 3) {
      result.push(numbers[i]);
    }
  }

  return result;
}
```

